4FFDE9BF43A27FBF02A9EDB5BF236E9B:
<Heading>Challenges</>

<stronger>Challenges</> are special, repeatable quests that increase in difficulty every time you complete them.

Each <stronger>Challenge</> quest line has <stronger>20 Stages</> to test your mettle!
29D49AE344F4D138F995ABB7B93F4CDB:
<Heading>Collection Book</>

Move extra people and schematics to your <stronger>Collection Book</> to earn <stronger>Collection Book XP</>.
Items in the <stronger>Collection Book</> can be leveled up and evolved for additional <stronger>Collection Book XP</>.
Collect rewards every time the <stronger>Collection Book</> levels up!

You can spend <stronger>V-bucks</> to unslot items in the <stronger>Collection Book</>. But you will lose <stronger>Collection Book XP</> when you unslot items in the <stronger>Collection Book</>.

Most heroes can be recruited from the <stronger>Collection Book</> with <stronger>Flux</> and <stronger>Training Manuals</>. 
Most schematics can be researched from the <stronger>Collection Book</> with <stronger>Flux</> and <stronger>Weapon Designs</> or <stronger>Trap Designs</>.
2C50E0AC4C33501D2FE523B0CEE9909E:
<Heading>Daily Quests</>

Every day, you are assigned a <stronger>Daily Quest</>. Completing the <stronger>Daily Quest</> will reward you with <stronger>V-bucks</> and <stronger>Gold</>.

You can have up to 3 active <stronger>Daily Quests</> at a time and you can abandon 1 per day if you want to try something new.

In order to get new <stronger>Daily Quests</>, you'll need to complete your active quests.
E63399814FEEB79592758B8DAED442AA:
<Heading>Defenders</>

Need a hand on your current mission? Defenders can be summoned during the mission to fill in for any missing players in your party to help take out those pesky husks.

Build <stronger>Defender Pads</> while you're in a mission, then activate them to call a defender. In a Storm Shield Defense mission, you can summon additional defenders to create a small army!
50AFE9FA417116538EC7A08F1F2D6DC5:
<Heading>Do I get to keep the cosmetic items I earned forever?</>

Yes.

The <stronger>exclusive cosmetic items</> you earn from a Battle Pass are yours to <stronger>keep forever</> and will <stronger>not be obtainable again</>.
463908C14FA011DB910AE3A25CBC2F89:
<Heading>Does my progress count if I buy the Battle Pass mid-season?</>

Yes. Buying the Battle Pass will <stronger>unlock all Battle Pass rewards up to the current Tier</> that you've reached. Keep in mind, however, that buying a Battle Pass early will allow you to earn <stronger>Battle Stars</> faster.

<strong>NOTE</> - Depending on the amount of time remaining in the season, you may not be able to earn all Battle Pass rewards just by completing the remaining Missions.
E3B00B614C3F33591312419DCE08CB66:
<Heading>Does the Battle Pass expire?</>

Yes. The Battle Pass expires at the <stronger>end of Season X</>.

Although you will <stronger>keep all in-game cosmetic rewards</> that you have earned, your XP boosts will end and you no longer have the opportunity to earn more rewards or complete Weekly Challenges from that season.
C3A87A814DB1C2F0CB0B02BC2315D28E:
<Heading>Expedition Squads</>

Don’t leave your heroes standing around idle, send them on an <stronger>expedition</> and watch the rewards roll in!

Select an <stronger>expedition</> with rewards you like.

Choose heroes to send. Chance of success depends on how the <stronger>combined power of the heroes</> match with the <stronger>expedition requirements</>.

Your heroes will return later with rewards! 

<stronger>Heroes on expedition will be unavailable elsewhere until they return.</>
E282E6C24C3F13B362FAF287BA7048CC:
<Heading>Hero Loadout</>

Select and assign a hero as your <stronger>Commander</> for your next mission. Up to 5 heroes can be assigned to the <stronger>Support Team</> and each of them adds 8% of their health, shield and ability damage stats to your Commander.

<Heading>Hero Perks</>

The Commander and each member of the <stronger>Support Team</> have <stronger>Hero Perks</> that may boost the Commander's combat performance in different ways.

<Heading>Team Perk</>

Assign a <stronger>Team Perk</> to the <stronger>Team Perk Slot</> to further improve your Commander's combat performance. With the right heroes assigned to the <stronger>Support Team</>, the bonuses granted by the <stronger>Team Perk</> can be further increased.
CBDD65D34E0F89AF1D2FD18EEDEE3453:
<Heading>How can I buy Battle Pass Tiers?</>

Once you own the <stronger>Battle Pass</>, you can choose to directly purchase <stronger>Tiers</> and immediately get the <stronger>Free Pass</> and <stronger>Battle Pass</> Rewards for those Tiers.

To purchase one or more <stronger>Tiers</>:
 1) Select the Tier in the Battle Pass tab that you want to purchase up to
 2) Choose "Buy Tiers"
 3) Adjust the number of Tiers that you'd like to purchase (Optional)
 4) Select the "Purchase" option
5FDAE90E4CDD51A337C4F482570AE054:
<Heading>How do I buy the Battle Pass?</>

Head to the <stronger>Battle Pass</> tab and select the "Buy Battle Pass" option. You'll then be able to use your V-Bucks to purchase the <stronger>Battle Pass</> or the <stronger>Battle Pass Bundle</>.

Need more V-Bucks? Grab some from the Store tab.
69EBD9B8486747001ED1EDB1E9F7C8CF:
<Heading>How do I collect Battle Stars?</>

<stronger>Battle Stars</> are one of several types of rewards that you can earn as you <stronger>complete Mission objectives</>. Earning <stronger>Battle Stars</> will unlock higher <stronger>Tiers</> in the Battle Pass.
EB589FDD41D72CDF3758658DF25CDF8B:
<Heading>How do I earn Battle Pass rewards?</>

Collecting <stronger>Battle Stars</> from <stronger>Missions</> will unlock higher <stronger>Tiers</> in the <stronger>Battle Pass</>.

<stronger>Some Tiers</> have a <stronger>Free Pass reward</> that everyone can earn. <stronger>All Tiers</> have at least one <stronger>Battle Pass reward</> that is only available to players that buy the Battle Pass.

Battle Pass owners earn both <stronger>Free Pass rewards</> and <stronger>Battle Pass rewards</>.
BA6F0DC548A773A1771999A2A7F56E1A:
<Heading>How do I equip the cosmetic items I earned?</>

The cosmetic items you earn are added to the <stronger>Locker</> tab.

To equip an item:
 1) Select an equipment or emote slot in the Locker tab.
 2) Select an item to preview it.
 3) Select the item again to equip it and save your selection.
B2747C034FE2FE0FA6897DBDD0BB35A9:
<Heading>Is the Battle Pass pay to win?</>

Nope.

The Battle Pass rewards are all cosmetic items that <stronger>do not affect gameplay</>.
869D091E4A78446D919837A4AF602312:
<Heading>Power</>

Your <stronger>Power</> is a measure of your overall combat effectiveness!

To increase your <stronger>Power</>, level up your <stronger>Account</>, level up and evolve the survivors in your <stronger>Survivor Squads</> and purchase <stronger>F.O.R.T. Stats</> in the <stronger>Research</> page.

<stronger>Party up with others</> to temporarily boost your Power even further!
591F637D4C540C367646A7947DCEB1DB:
<Heading>Quest Log</>

Your <stronger>Quest Log</> keeps a record of all your current quests and challenges, including those that you have completed in the past.

Complete quests to earn rewards, including special event exclusive or limited time rewards.

<stronger>Pin Quests</> to track your progress in game.
D2AF348F4613E21B93D368A9D5C22B5A:
<Heading>Research Page</>

Spend <stronger>Research Points</> to increase <stronger>F.O.R.T. Stats</> in the <stronger>Research Page</>.

<stronger>Research Points</> accumulate automatically over time, but you a have limited storage, so collect and spend them regularly.

The rate at which <stronger>Research Points</> accumulate and their storage limit increases at specific <stronger>Account Levels</>. So keep doing your quests and side missions to earn <stronger>Account XP</>.
74C8052A440E4197BC0D40B2553905BA:
<Heading>Save The World</>

<stronger>If you're out there, we need your help!</>

The storm came, and the monsters followed.  They took everything: our towns, even our families.  The few of us left are in serious danger... 

<stronger>Now it's time to fight back!  All we need is a leader.  And that's you.</>

Sure it'll be dangerous. I mean, yeah, there's monsters (a lot of monsters!) but we've got massive forts, killer traps, and piles of loot.  If we stick together, they don't stand a chance.

<stronger>This is our world, and it's time to take it back!</>
669678BC42CE2062409FF6B2DA0AB0B2:
<Heading>Schematics</>

<stronger>Schematics</> give you the ability to <stronger>craft items</> that can be used on missions.

Level up and evolve your schematics to increase the power of crafted items and unlock their <stronger>special perks</>.

Keep in mind that items from evolved schematics require rarer resources to craft.
D8DC49A547416FD2E7C9218882989EB0:
<Heading>Side Quests</>

<stronger>Side Quests</> are optional quests that you can choose to pursue if you're looking for an extra challenge!

Complete <stronger>Side Quests</> to receive high value rewards like <stronger>V-bucks</> and <stronger>Skill Points</>.

Each <stronger>Side Quest</> can only be completed once, but completing one may unlock access to a new, more challenging <stronger>Side Quest</>.
B501AAD540A5A77B2CC7A186D934DCD3:
<Heading>Storage</>

If you earn items as a mission reward, or collect resources on an Expedition, but don't have room in your backpack, items will instead be placed in <stronger>Storage</>.

As long as there is open room, you can move items freely between your backpack and your Storage. You can unlock more storage space through the <stronger>Upgrades Page</>.

Your <stronger>Storage</> can also be accessed from your <stronger>Stormshield</>.
69A31AE04F25882840CF499392A0B87E:
<Heading>Survivor Squads</>

Add Survivors to your <stronger>Survivor Squads</> to increase your Power and F.O.R.T. stats. The more powerful the Survivor, the more they benefit your squad. <stronger>Level up and evolve your Survivors</> to increase their power! 

Match Leaders to their <stronger>job type</> and <stronger>squad personalities</>, and pair up Survivors with similar <stronger>traits</> to gain additional bonuses.
E08C81C24E4217D781375888FCBDBDA8:
<Heading>Transform Keys</>

Use the magic of Vindertech to transform your extra schematics into that one specific schematic type you really need!

Select a <stronger>transform key</> that matches the type of schematic you want to create.

Add schematics from your <stronger>Armory</> until the transformation requirements are met.  Higher level and higher rarity schematics provide more transform power.

<stronger>Schematics used in the Transform process will be permenantly consumed!</>
A7D5953A4ED617A1D46BACA307A5D97C:
<Heading>Upgrades Page</>

Earn <stronger>Account XP</> by completing quests, side missions, and earning badges in game. The more activities your team completes within a mission, the more XP you will receive. Every time you fill up your <stronger>Account XP</> bar, you gain an <stronger>Account Level</>. <stronger>Upgrade Points</> are awarded at specific <stronger>Account Levels</>.

Spend <stronger>Upgrade Points</> in the <stronger>Upgrades Page</> to unlock new <stronger>Tools</> and <stronger>Gadgets</> or increase the level of existing <stronger>Tools</> and <stronger>Gadgets</>.

The requirement to purchase new <stronger>Tools</> and <stronger>Gadgets</> or increase the level of purchased <stronger>Tools</> and <stronger>Gadgets</> is determined by your <stronger>Account Level</>.
3B5AB032486B07A3A1F09EB624657FBC:
<Heading>What are Battle Bling rewards in the Battle Pass?</>

<stronger>Battle Bling</> are special cosmetic items worn on your outfit, weapons, and back bling that <stronger>show off your accomplishments</>. Some <stronger>Battle Bling</> are <stronger>“Reactive”</> and respond to events that happen during a Battle Royale match. Others are <stronger>“Progressive”</> and unlock new styles as you accomplish specific goals.

<stronger>Battle Bling</> can be equipped in the <stronger>Locker</> tab, but you cannot equip the same <stronger>Battle Bling</> in multiple slots.

<strong>NOTE</>- Some <stronger>Battle Bling</> must be equipped in order to make progress toward new styles.
7D22554740E11ED0AF098E8B222F3410:
<Heading>What are Missions?</>

A <stronger>Mission</> is a series of rewards and objectives. For each objective that you complete, you’ll move one point along the path of rewards. Potential rewards include <stronger>Battle Stars</>, <stronger>XP</>, and <stronger>cosmetic items</>.

<strong>NOTE</> - Some <stronger>Missions</> are only available to players that own the <stronger>Battle Pass</>.
AD4EB2914182860198C6E4B93140CBE5:
<Heading>What are Tiers? How are Tiers different than my Season Level?</>

<stronger>Tiers</> represent your progress in the Battle Pass. Collecting <stronger>Battle Stars</> from <stronger>Missions</> will unlock higher <stronger>Tiers</>.

<stronger>Season Levels</> represent your time playing during the current season. Collect <stronger>XP</> in Battle Royale matches to reach higher <stronger>Season Levels</>.
0D8DD8454E6FCEAF4ACF38BE455E4370:
<Heading>What are the Music rewards in the Battle Pass?</>

<stronger>Music</> rewards provide you with new musical tracks to listen to while in the <stronger>Lobby and other menus</>. After getting new <stronger>Music</>, it can be selected in the <stronger>Locker</> tab.
06292B294C7B7D19271966865BAAA9E4:
<Heading>What are the Pet rewards in the Battle Pass?</>

<stronger>Pets</> are cute animal partners that join your island adventures within the safety of a <stronger>special carrier on your back</>. After getting a <stronger>Pet</>, it can be selected as your Back Bling in the <stronger>Locker</> tab.
89A7693C49D7D56CE14D478026E27962:
<Heading>What are the Wrap rewards in the Battle Pass?</>

With <stronger>Wraps</>, you can <stronger>visually customize items</> that you find during Battle Royale matches. The categories of items that you can independently customize with Wraps include <stronger>Vehicles</>, <stronger>Assault Rifles</>, <stronger>Shotguns</>, <stronger>SMGs</>, <stronger>Sniper Rifles</>, <stronger>Pistols</>, and <stronger>Misc</> items.

After getting a <stronger>Wrap</>, it can be selected in the <stronger>Locker</> tab.
643F01E8438E105196109882C25B729C:
<Heading>What does Party Assist do?</>

Within the <stronger>Challenges Tab</>, you can turn on <stronger>Party Assist</> for a single <stronger>Mission Objective</> or <stronger>Challenge</>. Then, during a match, your <stronger>party members</> can help you complete that challenge!
EE41D27C4CB8253200EE7A82736C18E8:
<Heading>What does it mean to "Prestige" a Mission?</>

Some <stronger>Missions</> can be <stronger>Prestiged</> once you have completed <stronger>all of the objectives</>. <stronger>Prestiging</> a <stronger>Mission</> allows you to complete a new set of <stronger>harder objectives</> for even <stronger>more rewards</>.

<strong>NOTE</> - Not all Missions can be Prestiged.
DED49B914B13F577D83DBD8B65CDC954:
<Heading>What gets reset at the end of a season?</>

At the end of a season, all progress for that season's Levels and Battle Pass will stop.

Although you will <stronger>keep all in-game cosmetic rewards</> that you have earned, your XP boosts will end and you no longer have the opportunity to earn more rewards or complete Missions from that season.
39AA48034A6D91F7281C098C7FDEB2EE:
<Heading>What is the Battle Pass?</>

The <stronger>Battle Pass</> is a way to earn <stronger>exclusive in-game rewards</> by playing Battle Royale during <stronger>Season X</>.

These rewards include: outfits, gliders, harvesting tools, pets, back bling, emotes, sprays, toys, wraps, contrails, music, loading screens, and more.

Purchasing the <stronger>Battle Pass</> also unlocks many <stronger>Missions</> throughout the season. By completing the objectives in these <stronger>Missions</>, you'll progress through the <stronger>Battle Pass</> and earn even <stronger>more rewards</>.

All in-game items that you unlock are yours to <stronger>keep forever</>!
243B770248E1F0D7B62571BB4814B072:
<Heading>What's the difference between Free Pass rewards and Battle Pass rewards?</>

<stronger>Free Pass rewards</> are available to all players; no purchase necessary.

<stronger>Battle Pass rewards</> are only available to players that buy the Battle Pass with V-Bucks.

<strong>NOTE</> - Purchasing the Battle Pass after unlocking higher tiers will <stronger>grant all earned Battle Pass rewards</>.
FD097A024FDA13EFFDEE54BFD0FD40B4:
<Heading>XP Boosts</>

When an <stronger>XP Boost</> is active, you will receive <stronger>Account XP</> at an increased rate.  There are two different ways to boost your XP: You can apply an XP Boost from the <stronger>BOOSTS!</> menu, or you can be boosted by (or send a boost to) a <stronger>teammate</>.

Additionally, everyone receives <stronger>Daily Bonus XP</> just for playing the game.  Every point of XP you earn will be doubled until your Daily Bonus XP is exhausted, and the boost resets once per day.

<heading>How do XP Boosts work?</>

There are two types of XP Boosts: <stronger>Personal XP Boosts</> and <stronger>Friend XP Boosts</>. Both of these boosts are Battle Pass rewards that do not expire until the end of the season. 

 - <stronger>Personal XP Boosts</> increase the amount of XP you earn after a match of Battle Royale.

 - <stronger>Friend XP Boosts</> increase the amount of XP you earn after a match of Battle Royale when you play with one or more friends.

Owning the Battle Pass and playing with friends will maximize how quickly you Level Up.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Auto Decline Friend Requests</> 
Incoming friend requests will be automatically declined.  This will prevent players from potential spam friend requests and unknown player names.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: In order to friend other players, you will have to temporarily disable this, or this account must send the invite.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Player can not receive friend requests.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: Player receives all friend requests as normal.
881EF04C49A4EAAAF4C70ABE81081573:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Filter Mature Language</> 
In Fortnite Battle Royale players can text chat with friends in their squad when in the lobby.

In Fortnite Save The World players can text chat with friends in the lobby, and with any other players in a private or public match. 

This option lets you filter mature language in the chat, both that you send and receive from others.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Mature language in text chat will be filtered and replaced with heart symbols.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: Mature language can appear in text chat.
0F55ACA0448110F2FDA2B7B9390BE1A8:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Hide Non-Squad Member Names</> 
During a match, the account names of players who are eliminated will appear on the screen. 

This setting allows you to replace the names of other players who are not in your squad with "Player" in those messages.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: You will still be able to see the names of people in the same "squad" (up to three other players on your team who may or may not be friends).

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Replaces the names of players that are not in your squad with "Player".

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: You will see the names of players that are not squad members.
755EB5C844F89D0A73A23A9F0A771F53:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Hide Your Name from Non-Squad Members</> 
During a match, the account names of players who are eliminated will appear on the screen. 

This setting allows you to replace your name with "Player" in these messages for everyone who is not in your squad.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: People in the same "squad" (up to three other players on your team who may or may not be friends) will still be able to see your account name.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Replace your name to players that are not in your squad with "Player".

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: Players that are not in your squad will be able to see your account name.
8853D9A34F9CC7A03F3518AC0ACC15FC:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Purchase Notifications</> 
As an optional service, you can receive a notification sent to the email associated with this account whenever there is a real-money transaction to purchase V-Bucks or other items.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: Click on "More Settings" below to learn about spending restrictions on your platform.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: Notifications will be sent.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: No notifications will be sent.
4B0294B74FE5BE57B6888182313047A0:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Text Chat</> 
While in a party with friends or when teamed up with random players during a match, a text chat channel becomes available. This setting controls whether or not this account can receive or send messages in the text chat channel.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: This setting disables Fortnite’s in-game text chat. The platform you are playing on may have additional communication features that must be restricted separately. For information on platform specific controls please use the "More Settings" button.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: You can send and receive text chat messages with your teammates.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: You cannot send or receive text chat messages with your teammates.
55A359AB4C4DDFE456701996AF2694B2:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Voice Chat</> 
While in a party with friends or when teamed up with random players during a match, a voice chat channel becomes available. This setting controls whether or not this account can hear and talk in that voice chat channel.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: This setting disables the Fortnite’s in-game voice chat. The platform you are playing on may have additional communication features that must be restricted separately. For information on platform specific controls please use the "More Settings" button.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: You can hear your teammates and talk to them using a microphone.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: You cannot hear or talk to teammates.
A864CD3F44C02A0B2B78CF8B63132B0A:
<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="22">Weekly Playtime Reports</> 
As an optional service, a weekly playtime report can be generated and sent to the email associated with this account.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Note</>: Click on "More Settings" below to learn about playtime restrictions on your platform.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">On</>: A weekly report will be sent to the email address associated with this account.

<text color="00FFD6FF" fontface="black" case="upper" size="20">Off</>: No reports will be sent.

Created by AlanShinohara! Knock Town was a top 3 contender for the LTM Creator Contest.

Use the grappler to jump around and dodge shots as you one-tap enemies in the air with the Flint-Knock Pistol. 

The player with the most eliminations at the end of the round wins!
F2F2D8B04839E7960D68CD999A931083:
Created by BluDrive and Tolmollia! Echo Point was a top 3 contender for the LTM Creator Contest.

Destroy each objective to advance. If the attacking team reaches the final objective before time runs out, they win! Watch out for secret passages, attackers can use them to sneak around the front line. 

Each objective is marked with a red arrow.

F381FE45408F26D35B0AC8A9C51E7A7A:
Created by Prudiz

The war is almost over. Storm the beach defenses and destroy the doomsday cannon, or stage a last-ditch defense to keep the invaders at bay.

Attackers: Assault the beach, destroy the sentries and reach the forward checkpoint then assault the objective. Look for extra ways into the compound.

Defenders: Get to the wall and help your sentries repel the invaders. Fall back when you must and try to protect the objective for 15 minutes.
403BA47D4310384CAAB31CA8F060D328:
Created by Stray Kite

Hide and Seek with a twist!  Play 2 rounds, switching roles between rounds.  The team with the most points wins!

The Prop team must disguise themselves with the Prop-o-matic to avoid detection. Collect coins to score 1 point. Props make a sound every 15 seconds.

The Hunter team must use their wits and their weapons to find and eliminate the pesky props. Eliminations are worth 2 points.
6D42CF2A4110C23C0E3EE9B06725845F:

Battle the other squads to claim the most points from the capture zones!
Climb to the top of the Fast Food towers while protecting your blade holder!
Use impulse grenades and other power ups to blast other teams out of the capture zones!

Chitauri will respawn when eliminated until their army is decimated. They must help Thanos find the stones before this happens to achieve victory.

When playing Fortnite Battle Royale we ask you to agree to the following code of conduct:

(TLDR: Respect other players and play fair, simple right?)

1. <Font.Emph>Respect other players.</> Be graceful in victory and defeat. Discriminatory language, hate speech, threats, spam, and other forms of harassment or illegal behavior will not be tolerated.

2. <Font.Emph>Play fairly and within the rules of the game.</> Don’t cheat, AFK, grief, exploit bugs or glitches, team up in groups larger than the game mode allows (e.g. in solo matches do not work with other players, respectfully eliminate them instead) or impersonate others.

3. <Font.Emph>Keep account information safe and private.</> Giving access to your account puts you at risk. Do not share your account information or the account information of others.

4. <Font.Emph>Good luck and have fun!</>
If you see players not respecting the FBR code, please reach out to us in-game via the report a player button or by contacting player support . We will investigate all feedback and take action if or when necessary.

The Fortnite Battle Royale Code is not final and will change over time, make sure you are checking back to stay up to date.

“But, I didn’t know…” is not a valid excuse, and honestly a pretty bad one. We’re all here to have fun and enjoy the game!

FortSetting.ResolutionScale_Description: 3D resolution determines the resolution that objects are shown in game. This does not affect the main menu.
FortSetting.VoiceChatMethod_Description:
<strong>Push To Talk</>: Push To Talk.

<strong>Open Mic</>: Open Mic
FortSetting.ResolutionForcedNative: <strong>Windowed Fullscreen</> requires resolution match the native desktop resolution.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalBoostSpeedAds_Description: Additional left/right rotation speed applied when stick is fully deflected while aiming down sights.  Allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalBoostSpeed_Description: Additional left/right rotation speed applied when stick is fully deflected.  Allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.
FortSetting.LookVerticalBoostSpeedAds_Description: Additional up/down rotation speed applied when stick is fully deflected while aiming down sights.  Allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.
FortSetting.LookVerticalBoostSpeed_Description: Additional up/down rotation speed applied when stick is fully deflected.  Allows for quicker turns while maintaining look precision.
FortSetting.UserInterfaceContrast_Description: Adjust the contrast of the user interface.
FortSetting.CinematicVolume_Description: Adjusts the volume of cinematics or cut scene videos.
FortSetting.SoundEffectsVolume_Description: Adjusts the volume of sound effects.
FortSetting.VoiceChatVolume_Description: Adjusts the volume of voice chat.
FortSetting.PostProcessingQuality_Description: After scenes are loaded in the game, the images are further processed, improving the visual quality. Lowering this setting can raise the frame rate with only minor impact on quality. Using a lower resolution also benefits the post processing performance.
FortSetting.AllowLowPower_Description: Allows the game to automatically reduce settings to preserve power.
FortSetting.LockPrimaryInputMethodToMouse_Descriptio: Allows using Controller Input and Mouse Input together, and locks the input feedback to Mouse and Keyboard suggestions, rather than having the input methods fight.
FortSetting.AnonymousCharacterMode_Description: Alters your cosmetic loadout that will appear for opponents during a match. You will still appear as your selected cosmetics to yourself and teammates.
FortSetting.AntiAliasing_Description: Anti-Aliasing smooths edges on 3D objects in-game. Increasing this setting will make edges look smoother, but can reduce performance. Higher settings mean more anti-aliasing.
FortSetting.LogoutBody: Are you sure you want to log out of Fortnite?
FortSetting.VoiceChatInputDevice_Description: Changes the voice chat input device, the device with a microphone that will receive your voice chat that teammates will hear.
FortSetting.VoiceChatOutputDevice_Description: Changes the voice chat output device, where you will hear your teammates that are using voice chat.
FortSetting.HiddenMatchmakingDelay_Description: Creates a random small delay during matchmaking and hides matchmaking status updates to limit repeat in-game harassment. The random delay is chosen between 0 and the number of seconds selected. Each attempt to play will randomly generate a delay. NOTE: Enabling this setting will cause longer queue times.
FortSetting.Resolution_Description: Display Resolution determines the size of the window in Windowed mode. In Fullscreen mode, Display Resolution determines the graphic card output resolution, which can result in black bars depending on monitor and graphic card. Display Resolution is inactive in Windowed Fullscreen mode.
FortSetting.ShowFPS_Description: Enable this to show the frames per second. Use this to help gauge the effect of adjusting different video settings.
FortSetting.UseLegacyControls_Description: Enable to revert back to the legacy controller behavior.
FortSetting.ShowVoiceIndicators_Description: Enables / Disables the notifications that appear when someone in your voice channel speaks.
FortSetting.UseAdvancedOptions_Description: Enables fine-tuning of look controls.  Disables basic settings.  Use with caution!
FortSetting.RecievePlayerSurveys_Description: Enables or disables whether or not you are willing to receive periodic player surveys from Epic Games. Player surveys help guide the development of Fortnite, and generally you should not receive more than about one per month.
FortSetting.Vsync_Description: Enabling Vsync eliminates screen tearing by always rendering and presenting a full frame. Disabling Vsync can give higher frame rate and better input response, but can result in horizontal screen tearing. This feature only works if 'Window Mode' is set to 'Fullscreen'.
FortSetting.FrameRateLimit_Description: Frame rate limit sets the highest frame rate that is allowed. Set this lower for a more consistent frame rate or higher for the best experience on faster machines. You may need to disable Vsync to reach high frame rates.
FortSetting.HideOtherPlayerNames_Description: Hides names of players that are not squad members.  Their names will still be tracked for player reporting.
FortSetting.AnonymousMode_Description: Hides your name from other players.  Your name will still be tracked for player reporting.
FortSetting.VisualEffectQuality_Description: Higher effects settings add details to certain objects and interactions in game. Increasing this setting will make these objects and interactions have more details, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.TextureQuality_Description: Higher textures settings give flat objects a more detailed appearance. Increasing this setting will make objects more detailed, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.AimAssistStrength_Description: How much aim assist to apply.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalSpeedAds_Description: How quickly your view rotates left and right while aiming down sights.
FortSetting.LookHorizontalSpeed_Description: How quickly your view rotates left and right.
FortSetting.LookVerticalSpeedAds_Description: How quickly your view rotates up and down while aiming down sights.
FortSetting.LookVerticalSpeed_Description: How quickly your view rotates up and down.
FortSetting.LookSensitivityPresetAds_Description: How quickly your view rotates while aiming down sights.
FortSetting.CrossplayPreference_Description: If enabled you can participate in parties and game modes with other platforms. If disabled, some game modes will be unavailable, and others may have Limited Pools with longer queue times, lower match populations, or higher latency.
FortSetting.IgnoreGamepadInput_Description: Ignore all gamepad input.  If you are using a input remapping tool, remapping controller input to keyboard keys, and don't want the game to also recieve the controller input.
FortSetting.StatbilizeLookInput_Description: Improves view stability when looking along the horizontal or vertical axis.
FortSetting.LifetimeRefundRequests_Description: In cases where you unintentionally purchase an item with V-Bucks, you have 3 lifetime Return Requests.Only items purchased within the last 30 days are eligible.  Consumable items – such as the Battle Pass, Battle Pass Tiers, or Llamas – are not returnable.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityMultiplierForAircraft_Na: Mouse Sensitivity Multiplier For Aircraft Steering
FortSetting.AllowMultithreadedRendering_Description: Multithreaded rendering splits drawing work across multiple threads which can dramatically improve performance on multi-core processors. This can cause hitches and lower FPS on weaker hardware.
FortSetting.VideoQuality_Description: Quality Preset allows you to adjust multiple video options with a single click. Try a few options to see what fits your preference and computer's performance. You can further refine these settings in the options below.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityMultiplierForAircraft_De: Regular mouse sensitivity settings are multiplied by this value when steering an aircraft by mouse
FortSetting.MobileFPSType_Description: Select a desired framerate. Use this to fine tune performance on your device.
FortSetting.GyroYawAxis_Description: Selects the axis used for Yaw rotation with motion controls.
FortSetting.Region_Description: Selects which server you wish to connect to. Servers that are closer to you will generally have better performance. Selecting 'Auto' picks the server with the best connection.
FortSetting.SendMobileNotifications_Description: Sends a push notification to friends on Mobile devices when you begin playing.
FortSetting.GyroSensitivity_Description: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while not targeting.
FortSetting.GyroScopedSensitivity_Description: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while targeting with scoped weapons.
FortSetting.GyroTargetingSensitivity_Description: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while targeting.
FortSetting.GyroHarvestingToolSensitivity_Descriptio: Sensitivity of Motion Controls while using the Harvesting Tool.
FortSetting.SafeZone_Description: Set the UI safe zone for the platform.
FortSetting.TouchDragSensitivity_Description: Set the sensitivity of touch and drag. With higher settings the camera will move faster when dragging to look around.
FortSetting.ToggleSprint_Description: Sets sprint to be a on/off toggle or a hold to sprint. When on, sprint is set to an on/off toggle with one press.
FortSetting.SprintByDefault_Description: Sets sprint to be the default movement mode. When on, you will automatically sprint when moving, and the 'sprint' control will make you walk.
FortSetting.ToggleTargeting_Description: Sets targeting to be an on/off toggle or a hold. When on, the targeting control will be an on/off toggle. Turning off sets the targeting control to be a hold.
FortSetting.RudderDeadZone_Description: Sets the dead zone of the rudder control.
FortSetting.DefaultFilledMatchAudioChannel_Descripti: Sets the default Voice Channel for matches in which the empty slots are Filled with random players.
FortSetting.RudderMaxThrottle_Description: Sets the max throttle point of the rudder control.
FortSetting.GamepadBuildingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for controller sensitivity when in build mode. 1.0 will have no change when in build mode. Lower settings will have more slow down when in build mode, and higher settings will increase sensitivity when in build mode.
FortSetting.GamepadEditModeMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for controller sensitivity when in edit mode. 1.0 will have no change when in edit mode. Lower settings will have more slow down when in edit mode, and higher settings will increase sensitivity when in edit mode.
FortSetting.GamepadTargetingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing controller sensitivity when targeting. 1.0 will have no slow down when targeting. Lower settings will have more slow down when targeting.
FortSetting.GamepadScopedMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing controller sensitivity when using a scope. 1.0 will have no slow down when using a scope. Lower settings will have more slow down when scoped.
FortSetting.MouseTargetingMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing mouse sensitivity when targeting. 1.0 will have no slow down when targeting. Lower settings will have more slow down when targeting.
FortSetting.MouseScopedMultiplier_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing mouse sensitivity when using a scope. 1.0 will have no slow down when using a scope. Lower settings will have more slow down when scoped.
FortSetting.TouchDragTargetingSensitivity_Descriptio: Sets the modifier for reducing touch and drag sensitivity when targeting. 1.0 will have no slow down when targeting. Lower settings will have more slow down when targeting.
FortSetting.TouchDragScopedSensitivity_Description: Sets the modifier for reducing touch and drag sensitivity when using a scope. 1.0 will have no slow down when using a scope. Lower settings will have more slow down when scoped.
FortSetting.ControllerLookSensitivityPitch_Descripti: Sets the sensitivity of the controller stick's vertical (y) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking up and down with the controller stick.
FortSetting.ControllerLookSensitivityYaw_Description: Sets the sensitivity of the controller sticks' horizontal (x) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking left and right with the controller stick.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityYaw_Description: Sets the sensitivity of the mouse's horizontal (x) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking left and right with the mouse.
FortSetting.MouseSensitivityPitch_Description: Sets the sensitivity of the mouse's vertical (y) axis. With higher settings the camera will move faster when looking up and down with the mouse.
FortSetting.HUDScale_Description: Sets the size of heads up display (HUD) elements. 1.0 will show the default HUD size. Lower settings will make HUD elements smaller.
FortSetting.SoundQuality_Description: Sets the sound quality. 'High' quality sounds better, but may decrease performance.
FortSetting.ShowGrass_Description: Shows grass in the game, which can reduce performance on slower machines. Disable to hide grass and improve performance.
FortSetting.MotionBlur_Description: Some people are very sensitive to motion blur. Disable this effect to prevent nausea or keep it enabled to get more fluent animations.
FortSetting.Shadows_Description: The Shadows setting determine how much shadow is shown for objects in the game. Shadows improve the look and give better depth perception, but can reduce performance.
FortSetting.EditButtonHoldTime_Description: The duration to hold the button for entering Edit Mode.
FortSetting.LookEaseTime_Description: Time it takes to ramp in look rotation after leaving the stick deadzone.  Allows for small view adjustments by tapping the stick.
FortSetting.LookBoostAccelerationTime_Description: Time it takes to reach the boost speed when stick is fully defected.
FortSetting.LookBoostAccelerationTimeAds_Description: Time it takes to reach the boost speed when stick is fully deflected while aiming down sights.
FortSetting.AutoEquipBetterItems_Description: Turn auto equip better items on/off. When on, better items will automatically be equipped when they are received.
FortSetting.ShowBackpack_Description: Turn on/off display of your own hero's backpack if they have any.
FortSetting.ShowHeadAccessories_Description: Turn on/off display of your own hero's head accessories if they have any.
FortSetting.ShadowPlayHighlights_Description: Turns NVIDIA highlights on/off. When on, NVIDIA highlights are automatically recorded for certain game events, like winning, getting eliminations, or being eliminated. This feature requires specific NVIDIA hardware.
FortSetting.AimAssist_Description: Turns aim assist on/off. When on, this helps attract your aim towards enemy players when using a controller.
FortSetting.InvertPitchForAircraftSecondary_Descript: Turns aircraft mouse steering inversion on/off. When on, moving the mouse forward will pitch the aircraft down.
FortSetting.InvertPitchForAircraftPrimary_Descriptio: Turns aircraft steering inversion on/off. When on, pressing forward will pitch the aircraft down.
FortSetting.AutoChangeMaterial_Description: Turns auto material change on/off. When on, you will automatically swap to a new material type when you try to build but do not have enough of the currently selected material.
FortSetting.AutoOpenDoors_Description: Turns auto open doors on/off. When on, doors will automatically open when you approach them.
FortSetting.AutoPickupWeaponsConsolePC_Description: Turns auto pick up weapons on/off. When on, weapons will automatically be picked up when moving over them, unless your inventory is full.
FortSetting.AutoPickupWeapons_Description: Turns auto pick up weapons on/off. When on, weapons will automatically be picked up when moving over them, unless your inventory is full.
FortSetting.AutoSortConsumablesToRight_Description: Turns auto sort consumables to right on/off. When on, consumable items such as health and shields will default to the rightmost empty quickbar slot when picked up.
FortSetting.GamepadAutoRun_Description: Turns controller auto-run on/off. When on, double clicking the movement stick will make you automatically run forward without needing to hold the stick forward.
FortSetting.EditModeAimAssist_Description: Turns edit mode aim assist on/off. When on, this attracts your controller aim to the closest editing square in building edit mode.
FortSetting.BackgroundAudio_Description: Turns game audio on/off when the game is in the background. When on, the game audio will continue to play when the game is minimized, or another window is focused.
FortSetting.ShowGlobalChat_Description: Turns global chat on/off. When on, you will see and be able to send messages in global chat.
FortSetting.InvertPitch_Description: Turns look inversion on/off. When on, your character will look down when the control is moved up.
FortSetting.CreativeTurboDelete_Description: Turns on/off the ability to rapidly delete things in creative mode by holding down the delete button.
FortSetting.PeripheralLighting_Description: Turns peripheral lighting on/off for supported devices.
FortSetting.ReplayRecordingCreativeMode_Description: Turns replay recording on/off for Creative Mode matches. Recording creative replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.ReplayRecordingLargeTeams_Description: Turns replay recording on/off for large team modes. When on, replays are recorded and stored after each match with large teams, such as 50v50 or Teams of 20. Recording large team replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.ReplayRecording_Description: Turns replay recording on/off. When on, replays are recorded and stored after each match. Recording replays can reduce performance and take up hard drive space.
FortSetting.EquipFirstBuildingPieceWhenSwappingQuick: Turns reset building choice on/off. When on, switching to build mode will always bring up the first build piece. When off, the game will remember and bring up the last build piece you were using.
Turns reset building choice on/off. When on, switching to build mode will always bring up the first build piece. When off, the game will remember and bring up the last build piece you were using.
FortSetting.ShowViewerCount_Description: Turns spectator count on/off. When on, a count of players spectating you is shown on the in-game HUD in the lower left.
FortSetting.SprintCancelsReload_Description: Turns sprint cancelling reload on/off. When on, your character will stop reloading a weapon and sprint when sprinting is engaged.
FortSetting.TapInteract_Description: Turns tap to search/interact on/off. When on, search/interact will require a single press. When off, the search/interact control must be held for the duration of the timer.
FortSetting.VisualizeAudioSources_Description: Turns the visual radial indicator for some sounds on/off.  When on, you will see the visual radial indicator for some sounds, but in game sound will no longer pan or provide spatialization.
FortSetting.TurboBuild_Description: Turns turbo building on/off. When on, holding down the build button will automatically continue to build the selected piece when looking around. Turning off will set each building to require one press or click.
FortSetting.VoiceChat_Description:
Turns voice chat ON/OFF.

<strong>ON</>: You can hear your teammates and can also talk to them by using a microphone.

<strong>OFF</>: You cannot hear or talk to your teammates.
FortSetting.EnableRudderControl_Description: Use a Rudder Control device as input if connected.
FortSetting.UseRadialLookRates_Description: Uses the look stick direction to determine a single rotation speed for both horizontal and vertical rotation.  Allows for accurate diagonal aiming.
FortSetting.ColorBlindStrength_Description: Using the provided images, adjust the strength of the filter until you see the color correction that works best for you. There is a llama shape in the middle of each circle.
FortSetting.ColorBlindMode_Description: Using the provided images, test out the different color blind modes of the filter until you see the color correction that works best for you. There is a llama shape in the middle of each circle.
FortSetting.TouchVerticalSensitivity_Description: Vertical Sensitivity Multiplier for Touch Input.
FortSetting.ViewDistance_Description: View distance sets the distance from the player that other players and objects can be seen. Closer view distance can improve performance on slower computers, but further view distance can be an advantage in gameplay.
FortSetting.ConsoleUnlockedFPS_Description: When on, maximizes framerate but will lead to inconsistent performance and higher input lag.
FortSetting.PingPlaceDangerMarkerWhenTargeting_Descr: When placing a marker, if you are Targeting (ADS) when you ping, then a danger marker will be placed instead of the default location marker.
FortSetting.EnableTryBuildOnFocus_Description: When switching to a different build piece, using Builder Pro, it will try to build immediately.
FortSetting.WindowMode_Description: Window Mode allows you to select from 3 display window options. In Windowed mode you can interact with other windows more easily, and drag the edges of the window to set the size. In Windowed Fullscreen mode you can easily switch between applications. In Fullscreen mode you cannot interact with other windows as easily, but the game will run slightly faster.
